post_text: So PROUD! #olchspride 💚🤍💚🤍
shared_text:
Chris Repa is feeling thankful at Oak Lawn Chamber of Commerce.
June 15 at 9:01 AM · Oak Lawn, IL ·

Congratulations to Cross Countries and its outstanding executive board... President Thomas Karountzos, Vice-President Olivia Shell, Vice-President Tadgh Spillane, Treasurer Victoria Serna, and Secretary Ivan Zuniga! Their COVID-19 Local Business Relief Initiative netted nearly $12,000 over the past month. Last week these young leaders presented four Oak Lawn businesses each with a $3,000 gift. Recipients included Style 95 Barber Shop, Lyla Jewelers, AB Renovations, and Art Clay World USA. These funds will help provide comfort and assistance to employees and local residents during this difficult time. A HUGE thank you to the staff of Oak Lawn Community High School, Superintendent Dr. Michael Riordan, and the Oak Lawn Chamber of Commerce for their unbelievable support. The Chamber provided a matching gift after Cross Countries raised an initial $6,000 in donations. Without all of your efforts, none of this would have been possible. Please continue to support our local business community this summer and beyond. #olchspride #AllInIllinois #bethechange #TogetherWeRise

Congrats to Social Studies Student of the Quarter- Rosanne Caprio!

Rosanne is always engaged in class, and does a wonderful job helping her group members. Rosanne reached out to me in February to make me aware of some issues with another student in class because this student asked her to. That helped me seat the student in a better location and to understand how I could better help (that student) in my class. The fact that this student knew they could ask Rosanne for help and she did it in such a mature and appropriate way is outstanding. Rosanne even stayed on top of her work while out sick for over a week before the school closed.-Mrs. Herlihy
#olchspride

post_text:
The OLCHS “Cross Countries” organization is coordinating a relief effort to benefit local Oak Lawn businesses.

"Locked Down... But Not Out" is a virtual fundraiser to help raise money for local Oak Lawn businesses hit hardest by the global Covid-19 pandemic.

Donations to support the employees of these establishments will be accepted until May 15th and all money raised will be divided equally among as many businesses as we can support. Your consideration and generosity will go a long way in helping heal our community. Any donation, large or small, would be greatly appreciated!
#olchspride

https://www.gofundme.com/f/ol-relief

post_text: Oak Lawn Community High School students are eligible to participate in the community “Grab & Go” meal packages sponsored by Ridgeland School District 122 and Oak Lawn-Hometown School District 123. The meals are available to every OLCHS student and children ages 2-18 in the community. This program will provide a "Grab and Go" meal package that includes breakfast and lunch on a daily basis at no cost. Participation requires no advanced registration. Just show up to Oak Lawn Hometown Middle School 9AM-12PM or Simmons Middle School 9AM-11AM , grab, and go! For more information please refer to you OLCHS email to parents and students or visit our website.

text:
S.A.D.D. will be hosting Cinderella's Closet! We need your help with donations!!!
Please consider donating any slightly used formal dresses, shoes, accessories, and unopened make-up. All styles, sizes and colors are welcome. Donations can be dropped of at OLCHS in the District Office Rm 123 during business hours (7:30am-3:30pm) through Jan 31st, 2020.
Spread the word and clean out those closets to help make a girl's prom dream come true!

shared_text:
Oak Lawn Spartans Basketball
December 29, 2019 at 12:38 AM ·

Spartans capture 3rd place at the Effingham-Teutopolis Christmas Classic with a 69-64 Double OT win over Champaign Centennial. Trey Ward’s 32 led all scorers, while David Reyes went 10-10 from the charity stripe en route to 16 of his own. We battled! Not necessarily the 🏆 we wanted, but still good to come home with some hardware! Sami Osmani and Trey Ward were named to the all-tournament team. #SpartanHoops🏀 #olchspride
